The paper discusses a theory on the role of sex in evolution and its connection to the multiplicative weights update algorithm. This topic falls under the intersection of game theory, machine learning, and evolutionary biology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Making), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
